{
  "planText": "Add an Aircraft Tax Benefit Calculator as a new internal tools page in the existing React + Vite app without disrupting current routes, auth, or build. The work is split into safe, incremental steps. 1) Register a new React Router route at /tools/aircraft-tax and render it inside the existing AppLayout so it inherits navigation, auth, and styling. 2) Create a new page component that renders the page shell, title, and required disclaimer text, and acts as the integration point for the calculator wizard. 3) Introduce a self-contained calculator UI under a new aircraft-tax component folder, starting with a wizard controller and Step 1 use case routing UI that determines downstream steps. 4) Add a pure calculation library under client/src/lib/aircraftTax with no React imports, implementing depreciation, limitations, and cash flow logic using conservative defaults and guardrails. 5) Wire the wizard inputs to the calculation library and display results on the same page, including warnings, breakdowns, and JSON export. 6) Optionally add lightweight unit tests only for the pure calculation functions if a test runner is already present; otherwise document assumptions. 7) Add a short README or documentation section describing the calculator, assumptions, and disclaimers. Throughout, reuse shadcn/ui and Tailwind, avoid em dashes in UI text or comments, and keep all changes isolated to new files or minimal route wiring.",
  "files": [
    {
      "path": "client/src/App.tsx",
      "reason": "This file defines all React Router routes and is required to register the new /tools/aircraft-tax page within the existing application layout.",
      "changeSummary": "Import the AircraftTaxCalculator page and add a new Route wrapped in AppLayout for /tools/aircraft-tax.",
      "subtaskPrompt": "Add an import for the new AircraftTaxCalculator page and register a new <Route path=\"/tools/aircraft-tax\"> that renders it inside <AppLayout>, without modifying existing routes."
    },
    {
      "path": "client/src/pages/AircraftTaxCalculator.tsx",
      "reason": "This new page component serves as the top-level container for the Aircraft Tax Benefit Calculator and integrates it into the existing page and layout conventions.",
      "changeSummary": "Create a new page with title, required disclaimer text, and a placeholder mount point for the calculator wizard.",
      "subtaskPrompt": "Create this page component using existing Card and Alert components, include the exact disclaimer text, and prepare a section where the wizard component will be rendered."
    },
    {
      "path": "client/src/components/aircraft-tax/Wizard.tsx",
      "reason": "A dedicated wizard controller is needed to manage step state, branching logic, and progression without affecting other parts of the app.",
      "changeSummary": "Implement a local wizard state machine that controls which step component is shown based on the selected use case.",
      "subtaskPrompt": "Create a Wizard component that manages current step, shared form state, and conditional skipping of steps based on the Step 1 use case selection."
    },
    {
      "path": "client/src/components/aircraft-tax/StepUseCase.tsx",
      "reason": "Step 1 is a critical routing step that determines which downstream questions and calculations apply.",
      "changeSummary": "Add the Step 1 UI with radio options A through D and helper text, emitting the selected use case to the wizard.",
      "subtaskPrompt": "Implement a form step using shadcn/ui radio controls that asks whether the owner will fly in the placed-in-service year and reports the selected option upward."
    },
    {
      "path": "client/src/components/aircraft-tax/ResultsPanel.tsx",
      "reason": "Results must be displayed on the same page after calculation, including summaries, warnings, and export functionality.",
      "changeSummary": "Render calculated outputs, warnings, and an Export JSON button using existing Card, Alert, and Table components.",
      "subtaskPrompt": "Build a ResultsPanel component that accepts calculation results and input data, shows summary metrics and warnings, and implements a JSON download of inputs and results."
    },
    {
      "path": "client/src/lib/aircraftTax/types.ts",
      "reason": "Strong shared types are needed to keep the calculation engine pure, testable, and decoupled from React components.",
      "changeSummary": "Define TypeScript interfaces and enums for inputs, assumptions, classifications, and calculation results.",
      "subtaskPrompt": "Add TypeScript types for use case, activity classification, aircraft inputs, cost inputs, tax profile inputs, and calculation results with conservative optional fields."
    },
    {
      "path": "client/src/lib/aircraftTax/depreciation.ts",
      "reason": "Depreciation calculations are a core part of the calculator and must be isolated in pure functions.",
      "changeSummary": "Implement basis and first-year depreciation calculations using bonus and MACRS assumptions.",
      "subtaskPrompt": "Add pure functions to compute basis and first-year depreciation from provided inputs and assumptions, with no React or browser dependencies."
    },
    {
      "path": "client/src/lib/aircraftTax/limitations.ts",
      "reason": "Passive activity and excess business loss limitations need isolated, testable logic.",
      "changeSummary": "Implement passive loss absorption and excess business loss limit calculations.",
      "subtaskPrompt": "Create pure helper functions that apply passive loss limits and optional excess business loss caps, returning usable loss and carryforward amounts."
    }
  ]
}
```

